      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS ULTRA — single-image solve, maximum quality (no exports)\n\nThe shipping-MVP method at full quality: solve → shared depth → SAM3 sky → sky dome +\ntwo band clean-plate layers, all with the complete edge doctrine ON:\n  · relief_grid 1024 (ultra) + depth_edge_rel 1.5 on both band meshes\n  · edge_extend_px: plate colors smeared past every matte edge (sky 96 / bg 64 / fg 48)\n  · skirt_bevel 1.5: mesh boundaries RECEDE away from camera (45°+ beveled skirts) —\n    the extended colors land on the receding geometry instead of a hole or a cliff\n  · fill_occluded on bg: disocclusion depth synthesized behind the foreground\n  · sky frame_outpaint 128: orbits don't slam into the plate boundary\n  · exclude_mask (SAM sky) wired into EVERY layer — replaces the sky heuristic\n\nUSE: Queue once (1024-grid meshes on a 4K solve take a while) → in the viewport hit\n🧭 Safe Zone to MEASURE this scene's hole-free camera envelope (the orbit clamps to it)\n→ author your move inside those angles. 📽 Project is on by default.\n\nQA previews: bg hole_mask (where projection would show black) and bg extend_mask\n(invented/smeared pixels — in a DCC export these ship as {layer}_extend_matte.png).\n\nNOTES: swap the bg plate wire for a LaMa-inpainted clean plate for real disocclusion\ncontent (this graph projects the source photo as every plate). Two 1024-grid meshes\nare heavy in the browser — drop relief_grid to 512 if orbiting stutters. Indoor photo?\nSet BOTH depth_model widgets to the Indoor model."
      ]
    },
